1
00:00:09,666 --> 00:00:12,833
And so, parallel universes exist
not only in theory,

2
00:00:12,916 --> 00:00:14,875
but as an observable phenomenon.

3
00:00:14,958 --> 00:00:17,500
What an opportunity
that is for us.

4
00:00:17,583 --> 00:00:19,041
The amount of knowledge
we'll gain

5
00:00:19,125 --> 00:00:21,875
through that observance
will be undeniably valuable

6
00:00:21,958 --> 00:00:23,666
to the future of humanity.

7
00:00:23,750 --> 00:00:27,166
Here at the Research Laboratory
of Applied Physics,

8
00:00:27,250 --> 00:00:30,833
we continue to pursue
this vitally important work.

9
00:00:30,916 --> 00:00:33,583
We all wish things
could move more quickly.

10
00:00:33,666 --> 00:00:35,416
If the government loosened
its purse strings,

11
00:00:35,500 --> 00:00:37,458
then we could go faster
than a speeding tortoise.

12
00:00:37,541 --> 00:00:41,041
[laughter]

13
00:00:41,125 --> 00:00:42,875
Anyway, moving on...

14
00:00:42,958 --> 00:00:45,208
[TAIYO] This version of you
is quite verbose.

15
00:00:45,291 --> 00:00:46,625
[DAICHI scoffs]

16
00:00:46,708 --> 00:00:48,791
What do you think, Daichi,
can you do it?

17
00:00:48,875 --> 00:00:50,333
Don't you worry.

18
00:00:50,416 --> 00:00:52,708
Tomorrow he just needs to appear
as if nothing happened.

19
00:02:27,458 --> 00:02:29,666
♪

20
00:02:33,041 --> 00:02:34,333
[footsteps approaching]

21
00:02:37,791 --> 00:02:38,625
[DAICHI]
Hmm?

22
00:02:38,708 --> 00:02:40,166
Hey, good morning, chief.

23
00:02:40,250 --> 00:02:41,291
Coffee?

24
00:02:41,375 --> 00:02:43,208
Yeah, thanks a lot.

25
00:02:43,291 --> 00:02:44,416
[keyboard keys clack]

26
00:02:44,500 --> 00:02:45,458
[EIJI]
Whoa.

27
00:02:45,541 --> 00:02:46,791
Sugar.

28
00:02:46,875 --> 00:02:48,541
You usually add so much.

29
00:02:51,541 --> 00:02:53,916
I'm cutting back
after my last physical.

30
00:02:54,000 --> 00:02:56,375
Oh, man, guess that means
you're getting old.

31
00:02:56,458 --> 00:02:57,458
[DIRECTOR clears throat]

32
00:02:57,541 --> 00:02:59,166
How's the thesis looking?

33
00:02:59,250 --> 00:03:01,333
The conference
is coming up soon.

34
00:03:01,416 --> 00:03:02,708
[DAICHI]
Doing my best.

35
00:03:02,791 --> 00:03:04,750
Don't embarrass me,
you understand?

36
00:03:12,208 --> 00:03:13,500
-[computer chimes]
-Hmm?

37
00:03:20,833 --> 00:03:23,291
[indistinct chatter]

38
00:03:27,458 --> 00:03:28,750
[MIFUYU]
Thanks for waiting.

39
00:03:28,833 --> 00:03:30,208
Your omelet rice.

40
00:03:40,333 --> 00:03:41,708
[HEIJIRO]
Uh, excuse me, sir.

41
00:03:41,791 --> 00:03:43,625
-[DAICHI] Hmm?
-Negishi.

42
00:03:43,708 --> 00:03:46,875
And I'm here from the first
division of investigations.

43
00:03:46,958 --> 00:03:48,625
Hidaka.

44
00:03:48,708 --> 00:03:50,666
What do police want with me?

45
00:03:50,750 --> 00:03:52,250
[HEIJIRO]
Well, the skeletonized remains

46
00:03:52,333 --> 00:03:53,708
of three different men and women

47
00:03:53,791 --> 00:03:55,250
were found in
the Okutama Mountains

48
00:03:55,333 --> 00:03:56,416
just the other day.

49
00:03:56,500 --> 00:03:58,625
And as strange as it seems,

50
00:03:58,708 --> 00:04:00,500
because believe me,
I know it is,

51
00:04:00,583 --> 00:04:02,583
your dental records
are a perfect match

52
00:04:02,666 --> 00:04:03,875
to one of them.

53
00:04:03,958 --> 00:04:05,833
Even stranger than that
was the fact that,

54
00:04:05,916 --> 00:04:07,583
according to the examination,

55
00:04:07,666 --> 00:04:09,666
the victim you match with
had actually been dead

56
00:04:09,750 --> 00:04:11,958
for at least 50 years.

57
00:04:12,041 --> 00:04:14,666
So tell me,
how would you explain this?

58
00:04:16,166 --> 00:04:18,250
Honestly, shouldn't I
be asking you?

59
00:04:18,333 --> 00:04:20,375
I mean, you approached me
here, right?

60
00:04:20,458 --> 00:04:23,500
I'm not the one who's claiming
that I died 50 years ago.

61
00:04:23,583 --> 00:04:25,125
[HEIJIRO]
No, that's a fair point.

62
00:04:25,208 --> 00:04:27,166
I hope you'll accept my apology.

63
00:04:27,250 --> 00:04:28,625
You're a big shot scholar,

64
00:04:28,708 --> 00:04:31,416
so I was thinking maybe
you could shed some light.

65
00:04:31,500 --> 00:04:32,750
I'll come back again.

66
00:04:38,666 --> 00:04:41,291
Who were those guys
that were here just now?

67
00:04:41,375 --> 00:04:42,833
No one.

68
00:04:42,916 --> 00:04:44,708
Oh, and the director's calling.

69
00:04:44,791 --> 00:04:47,083
Wants to go over the thesis
before the conference.

70
00:04:47,166 --> 00:04:48,625
Probably.

71
00:04:48,708 --> 00:04:50,500
It'd be embarrassing if he
couldn't answer questions

72
00:04:50,583 --> 00:04:52,708
on the thesis
he supposedly wrote.

73
00:05:05,708 --> 00:05:07,916
[indistinct chatter]

74
00:05:08,000 --> 00:05:09,875
[SCIENTIST 1]
Wow, what do you think he did?

75
00:05:09,958 --> 00:05:12,833
[SCIENTIST 2]
Well, he dug the ladies, so...

76
00:05:12,916 --> 00:05:14,958
What a comfortable chair.

77
00:05:15,041 --> 00:05:17,375
His turn's coming up next.

78
00:05:17,458 --> 00:05:18,375
[MIFUYU]
Thanks for waiting.

79
00:05:18,458 --> 00:05:20,500
Your omelet rice.

80
00:05:20,583 --> 00:05:22,708
I had them leave out
the green peas.

81
00:05:23,708 --> 00:05:26,250
They aren't
to your liking, right?

82
00:05:26,333 --> 00:05:27,458
Hmm?

83
00:05:39,500 --> 00:05:40,916
You hear?

84
00:05:41,000 --> 00:05:42,791
The director's been expelled
from the conference

85
00:05:42,875 --> 00:05:44,083
due to plagiarism.

86
00:05:44,166 --> 00:05:45,083
Huh?

87
00:05:45,166 --> 00:05:46,958
He finally got what he deserved.

88
00:05:47,041 --> 00:05:50,458
So, congratulations
are in order, Mr. Director.

89
00:05:50,541 --> 00:05:51,958
[sighs]

90
00:05:52,041 --> 00:05:54,250
[indistinct chatter]

91
00:06:01,666 --> 00:06:03,458
And who might you be?

92
00:06:03,541 --> 00:06:05,250
♪

93
00:06:09,375 --> 00:06:11,000
[INSTRUCTOR]
We thank you for volunteering,

94
00:06:11,083 --> 00:06:12,833
despite the dangers.

95
00:06:12,916 --> 00:06:15,958
You all are the hope
of humanity.

96
00:06:16,041 --> 00:06:18,541
We pray for the success
of Project Noah.

97
00:06:18,625 --> 00:06:21,291
-[DAICHI grunts softly]
-Tell me this.

98
00:06:21,375 --> 00:06:23,541
Do you believe the predictions
of Nostradamus?

99
00:06:23,625 --> 00:06:25,791
[MAN] You mean the one where
the world's supposed to end?

100
00:06:25,875 --> 00:06:27,625
[scoffs]
No way.

101
00:06:27,708 --> 00:06:28,916
It's more fun not to.

102
00:06:29,000 --> 00:06:29,791
[MAN and WOMAN laugh]

103
00:06:29,875 --> 00:06:32,125
To senility from peace.

104
00:06:32,208 --> 00:06:35,458
All of that aside,
congratulations are in order.

105
00:06:35,541 --> 00:06:38,291
Now you've got control
over the laboratory.

106
00:06:38,375 --> 00:06:40,583
So you two were behind that,
after all.

107
00:06:40,666 --> 00:06:44,125
Yes, and we've completely
overtaken Lacuna Chemical, too.

108
00:06:44,208 --> 00:06:46,583
Leave the bioengineering to us.

109
00:06:46,666 --> 00:06:49,625
We've opened a route
to get the materials as well.

110
00:06:49,708 --> 00:06:51,125
Is that so?

111
00:06:51,208 --> 00:06:54,000
Now you can focus on
finishing the portal mechanism.

112
00:06:54,083 --> 00:06:56,833
There's no greater expert
in that field than you.

113
00:06:56,916 --> 00:06:58,541
We were the only ones

114
00:06:58,625 --> 00:07:01,416
who were able to successfully
transfer to this universe.

115
00:07:01,500 --> 00:07:03,500
Where could the other volunteers
have gone?

116
00:07:03,583 --> 00:07:05,541
[TSUKI gasps]

117
00:07:05,625 --> 00:07:06,625
Precisely.

118
00:07:06,708 --> 00:07:08,583
We can't worry about the method.

119
00:07:08,666 --> 00:07:10,875
Because if Project Noah
were to succeed,

120
00:07:10,958 --> 00:07:13,166
we'd be saving
millions of lives.

121
00:07:14,708 --> 00:07:16,666
[TSUKI]
To the future of our universe.

122
00:07:34,750 --> 00:07:36,958
We've been researching
the effect of surge particles

123
00:07:37,041 --> 00:07:38,416
on the human body.

124
00:07:38,500 --> 00:07:41,500
We've discovered
a rather surprising byproduct.

125
00:07:41,583 --> 00:07:42,791
What is it?

126
00:07:42,875 --> 00:07:46,333
Some children manifest
special abilities.

127
00:07:46,416 --> 00:07:47,875
Hmm. Interesting.

128
00:07:47,958 --> 00:07:49,916
I'll inform Daichi about this
as well.

129
00:07:50,000 --> 00:07:52,208
He could use it
to his advantage.

130
00:07:52,291 --> 00:07:53,625
No, don't.

131
00:07:53,708 --> 00:07:55,750
I want him to be
completely focused

132
00:07:55,833 --> 00:07:56,916
on the portal.

133
00:07:58,333 --> 00:08:00,125
Thank you for waiting.

134
00:08:00,208 --> 00:08:02,708
One number one, and one curry.

135
00:08:02,791 --> 00:08:03,958
Hope you enjoy.

136
00:08:05,083 --> 00:08:07,666
You know, she's really good
at her job.

137
00:08:07,750 --> 00:08:10,291
Mifuyu? Yeah, and she's
such a sweetheart.

138
00:08:10,375 --> 00:08:11,708
[SCIENTIST 1]
Oh, that reminds me,

139
00:08:11,791 --> 00:08:13,458
did you hear about her father?

140
00:08:13,541 --> 00:08:14,791
[SCIENTIST 2]
No, what?

141
00:08:14,875 --> 00:08:16,583
[SCIENTIST 1]
Look it up, you'll see.

142
00:08:16,666 --> 00:08:17,791
[MIFUYU]
Thanks for waiting.

143
00:08:17,875 --> 00:08:20,291
Your omelet rice.

144
00:08:20,375 --> 00:08:21,416
Uh...

145
00:08:21,500 --> 00:08:23,125
It's a little unbalanced.

146
00:08:24,458 --> 00:08:25,375
[sighs]

147
00:08:31,583 --> 00:08:33,458
Why are you
still looking into that?

148
00:08:33,541 --> 00:08:36,166
We can't even be sure
if it was a murder or not.

149
00:08:36,250 --> 00:08:38,458
And we'll have a hard time
finding evidence

150
00:08:38,541 --> 00:08:40,166
after 50 years.

151
00:08:40,250 --> 00:08:41,875
Yeah, but it bothers me.

152
00:08:43,625 --> 00:08:46,500
As I thought, our equipment
and budget are superior.

153
00:08:46,583 --> 00:08:49,000
No other lab in the country
could touch us.

154
00:08:49,083 --> 00:08:51,208
[TAIYO]
Our base has been decided.

155
00:08:51,291 --> 00:08:53,916
We're currently creating
an observation device.

156
00:08:54,000 --> 00:08:56,250
I'll convert it into a portal
and then, in theory,

157
00:08:56,333 --> 00:08:58,166
we should be able
to connect a path back

158
00:08:58,250 --> 00:08:59,625
to the other universe.

159
00:09:01,875 --> 00:09:03,000
But if we do,

160
00:09:03,083 --> 00:09:05,250
a giant void
will literally appear

161
00:09:05,333 --> 00:09:07,083
right in the middle of Tokyo.

162
00:09:08,083 --> 00:09:09,750
That's actually perfect, though.

163
00:09:09,833 --> 00:09:11,083
Keep in mind,

164
00:09:11,166 --> 00:09:12,916
we need an immense amount
of information

165
00:09:13,000 --> 00:09:14,458
to open the portal, right?

166
00:09:14,541 --> 00:09:15,791
So, in that sense,

167
00:09:15,875 --> 00:09:18,250
the more people
we involve, the better.

168
00:09:18,333 --> 00:09:20,833
Well, yes, that's true.

169
00:09:20,916 --> 00:09:22,500
It's not unlike this.

170
00:09:22,583 --> 00:09:24,250
The greater
the reciprocal recognition

171
00:09:24,333 --> 00:09:25,666
of the observers,

172
00:09:25,750 --> 00:09:28,000
the greater the opening.

173
00:09:28,083 --> 00:09:31,000
And millions of people are
all going to be seeking refuge,

174
00:09:31,083 --> 00:09:33,583
so the bigger the opening,
the better it is for them.

175
00:09:33,666 --> 00:09:35,250
Even now, as we speak,

176
00:09:35,333 --> 00:09:37,916
our universe
is falling into decay.

177
00:09:38,000 --> 00:09:41,458
Please, you have to complete
the portal as soon as possible.

178
00:09:58,208 --> 00:09:59,375
Thank you.

179
00:09:59,458 --> 00:10:00,291
[MIFUYU]
Sure.

180
00:10:04,166 --> 00:10:06,208
[DAICHI]
Man, I hate summer.

181
00:10:06,291 --> 00:10:07,541
[MIFUYU]
Yeah, same here.

182
00:10:07,625 --> 00:10:08,500
[DAICHI]
Hmm?

183
00:10:14,791 --> 00:10:16,125
[EIJI]
Daichi.

184
00:10:16,208 --> 00:10:17,375
I've read your thesis.

185
00:10:19,500 --> 00:10:22,333
This device can be used to
observe parallel universes,

186
00:10:22,416 --> 00:10:23,583
isn't that right?

187
00:10:23,666 --> 00:10:25,458
[DAICHI]
Yes, once it's finished.

188
00:10:25,541 --> 00:10:28,333
However, and correct me
if I'm wrong,

189
00:10:28,416 --> 00:10:30,166
but according to your thesis,

190
00:10:30,250 --> 00:10:32,708
it's possible to observe
and interact.

191
00:10:33,958 --> 00:10:36,541
This could be converted
to military use.

192
00:10:36,625 --> 00:10:39,708
Remember, science can be
poison or medicine

193
00:10:39,791 --> 00:10:41,666
depending on how it's used.

194
00:10:41,750 --> 00:10:42,833
Yeah, of course.

195
00:10:42,916 --> 00:10:44,625
This is a major opportunity.

196
00:10:44,708 --> 00:10:46,375
We've got work to do.

197
00:10:48,250 --> 00:10:50,833
[TAIYO] Increase the pace
of our human experimentation.

198
00:10:50,916 --> 00:10:53,791
[TSUKI sighs] There have
already been three this month.

199
00:10:53,875 --> 00:10:55,583
We need to try to locate humans

200
00:10:55,666 --> 00:10:58,291
who aren't affected
by the surge particles.

201
00:10:58,375 --> 00:11:00,791
They've got to be able to move
freely through the portals

202
00:11:00,875 --> 00:11:02,958
without losing
any of their memories.

203
00:11:03,041 --> 00:11:04,125
I understand.

204
00:11:04,208 --> 00:11:06,083
I'll speak with
the principal, then.

205
00:11:12,166 --> 00:11:13,500
Huh?

206
00:11:13,583 --> 00:11:14,500
Oh.

207
00:11:14,583 --> 00:11:15,791
You don't have to.

208
00:11:15,875 --> 00:11:17,375
I live really close by.

209
00:11:18,708 --> 00:11:20,041
[DAICHI]
I'd like to.

210
00:11:20,125 --> 00:11:21,500
[MIFUYU]
Hmm?

211
00:11:21,583 --> 00:11:23,000
Well, thanks.

212
00:11:23,083 --> 00:11:25,541
♪

213
00:11:30,583 --> 00:11:34,250
So, you're researching
parallel universes now,

214
00:11:34,333 --> 00:11:35,541
aren't you?

215
00:11:35,625 --> 00:11:36,791
Yes, that's right.

216
00:11:36,875 --> 00:11:38,458
Do you know what they are?

217
00:11:39,791 --> 00:11:41,291
Does their existence mean

218
00:11:41,375 --> 00:11:43,416
that there's another me
in another place?

219
00:11:43,500 --> 00:11:44,750
[DAICHI]
Yes.

220
00:11:44,833 --> 00:11:46,625
[MIFUYU] And versions
where I don't exist?

221
00:11:46,708 --> 00:11:48,166
[DAICHI]
That is a possibility.

222
00:11:49,791 --> 00:11:52,333
[MIFUYU] And we can actually see
these other universes?

223
00:11:53,375 --> 00:11:55,000
[DAICHI]
We will, in the near future.

224
00:11:58,958 --> 00:12:00,375
I'd love to see that.

225
00:12:03,458 --> 00:12:05,416
Oh, this is me.

226
00:12:05,500 --> 00:12:06,708
Thank you so much.

227
00:12:15,166 --> 00:12:17,125
[DAICHI gasps]

228
00:12:31,166 --> 00:12:32,958
[MIFUYU]
It's like this every year.

229
00:12:33,041 --> 00:12:35,541
Whenever it gets close
to the day of the accident.

230
00:12:36,750 --> 00:12:39,583
When I was a little girl,
I was very sickly.

231
00:12:39,666 --> 00:12:41,541
So, to pay for
the hospital bills,

232
00:12:41,625 --> 00:12:44,375
my dad forced himself
to drive strenuous hours.

233
00:12:45,791 --> 00:12:49,500
That's why, to me at least,
those words actually ring true.

234
00:12:51,625 --> 00:12:54,208
I would like to see a world
where I was never born.

235
00:12:54,291 --> 00:12:55,916
You know what I mean?

236
00:12:56,000 --> 00:12:58,583
If there really are
parallel universes.

237
00:13:00,375 --> 00:13:02,000
I'd give anything
to see my father

238
00:13:02,083 --> 00:13:03,916
still out there living his life.

239
00:13:04,000 --> 00:13:06,625
Working and doing the things
that made him happy.

240
00:13:19,625 --> 00:13:22,041
♪

241
00:14:00,458 --> 00:14:02,583
[WOMAN] Hey, where do you think
we should have the wedding?

242
00:14:02,666 --> 00:14:04,166
[MAN]
A chapel?

243
00:14:04,250 --> 00:14:05,875
[WOMAN] I'd love to be able
to see the ocean, though.

244
00:14:05,958 --> 00:14:07,208
[MAN]
Let's do Hawaii.

245
00:14:07,291 --> 00:14:08,625
-[WOMAN] Now you're talkin'.
-[MAN chuckles]

246
00:14:08,708 --> 00:14:10,625
♪

247
00:14:41,250 --> 00:14:42,208
[grunts softly]

248
00:14:42,291 --> 00:14:44,666
[door chimes]

249
00:14:44,750 --> 00:14:47,291
[TAIYO] Is the portal
still not finished?

250
00:14:47,375 --> 00:14:49,708
You should have been able
to complete that ages ago,

251
00:14:49,791 --> 00:14:51,458
and you know it.

252
00:14:51,541 --> 00:14:53,458
I'm sorry, but it really
isn't that simple.

253
00:14:53,541 --> 00:14:55,083
I'm concerned about you.

254
00:14:55,166 --> 00:14:58,791
Are you starting to develop
feelings for this universe?

255
00:14:58,875 --> 00:14:59,916
No way.

256
00:15:00,000 --> 00:15:01,875
[TAIYO]
Not even for that woman?

257
00:15:01,958 --> 00:15:03,208
[DAICHI gasps]

258
00:15:03,291 --> 00:15:05,166
You're well aware
of what you're doing.

259
00:15:05,250 --> 00:15:07,375
You understand what it means
to involve yourself

260
00:15:07,458 --> 00:15:10,083
with a human
from this universe.

261
00:15:10,166 --> 00:15:12,083
I believe in you, I really do.

262
00:15:12,166 --> 00:15:14,708
I know you'd never be
that kind of fool.

263
00:15:14,791 --> 00:15:16,583
The kind who values
a single woman

264
00:15:16,666 --> 00:15:19,541
over the lives of millions
waiting to be saved.

265
00:15:28,000 --> 00:15:29,250
What's wrong?

266
00:15:31,791 --> 00:15:34,375
Mifuyu, it's over.

267
00:15:34,458 --> 00:15:35,291
Huh?

268
00:15:36,666 --> 00:15:38,000
[DAICHI]
I'm sorry.

269
00:15:43,916 --> 00:15:45,083
[MIFUYU]
All right.

270
00:15:53,291 --> 00:15:54,208
Um...

271
00:15:56,958 --> 00:15:58,916
Take care of yourself, okay?

272
00:15:59,000 --> 00:16:00,208
[gasps softly]

273
00:16:33,916 --> 00:16:35,291
[sobbing quietly]

274
00:16:37,208 --> 00:16:38,333
-[door opens]
-[gasps]

275
00:16:38,416 --> 00:16:39,666
[panting]

276
00:16:49,291 --> 00:16:50,500
Hungry?

277
00:16:51,916 --> 00:16:52,875
[MIFUYU gasps]

278
00:16:55,875 --> 00:16:57,291
[MIFUYU]
Hey.

279
00:16:57,375 --> 00:16:59,208
[DAICHI]
Let's have kids.

280
00:16:59,291 --> 00:17:00,291
[MIFUYU gasps]

281
00:17:02,833 --> 00:17:05,416
[MIFUYU sobbing]

282
00:17:06,833 --> 00:17:08,958
♪

283
00:17:16,416 --> 00:17:17,958
[TAIYO]
Lacuna Chemical is a company

284
00:17:18,041 --> 00:17:20,875
that has always been ahead
of its own time.

285
00:17:20,958 --> 00:17:23,041
I hope that each of you
take real pride

286
00:17:23,125 --> 00:17:26,000
in your work
from this day on.

287
00:17:26,083 --> 00:17:28,500
I have high expectations
for all of you.

288
00:17:30,250 --> 00:17:32,083
Mifuyu!

289
00:17:32,166 --> 00:17:33,458
You're here.

290
00:17:33,541 --> 00:17:35,166
Congratulations.

291
00:17:35,250 --> 00:17:36,708
A beautiful girl.

292
00:17:38,083 --> 00:17:39,541
[gasps]

293
00:17:41,166 --> 00:17:44,083
Wow, her eyes
are exactly like yours.

294
00:17:46,916 --> 00:17:49,000
[MIFUYU]
Did you think of a name?

295
00:17:49,083 --> 00:17:50,208
[DAICHI]
Yeah.

296
00:17:50,291 --> 00:17:52,041
How about Yuki?

297
00:17:52,125 --> 00:17:53,375
[MIFUYU]
Yuki.

298
00:17:53,458 --> 00:17:55,583
Yes, I love it.

299
00:17:55,666 --> 00:17:56,708
[groans]

300
00:17:58,000 --> 00:18:00,333
Have you completely
lost your mind now?

301
00:18:00,416 --> 00:18:02,041
Don't you realize
what you've done?

302
00:18:02,125 --> 00:18:05,333
You've created a being
not fully from either universe.

303
00:18:05,416 --> 00:18:06,541
[DAICHI]
That's right.

304
00:18:06,625 --> 00:18:08,458
She carries the possibilities
of both.

305
00:18:08,541 --> 00:18:10,875
No. A human like
that shouldn't exist!

306
00:18:10,958 --> 00:18:12,583
Her very life
is a contradiction!

307
00:18:12,666 --> 00:18:14,875
She's a threat.

308
00:18:14,958 --> 00:18:16,458
-We have to get rid of her.
-[gasps]

309
00:18:16,541 --> 00:18:18,416
Just try and lay a hand
on my daughter,

310
00:18:18,500 --> 00:18:20,000
I'll kill you both myself!

311
00:18:20,083 --> 00:18:21,458
[TSUKI]
Hmm.

312
00:18:21,541 --> 00:18:24,000
You're really committed
to betraying us, then.

313
00:18:24,083 --> 00:18:26,500
Have you forgotten your duty?

314
00:18:26,583 --> 00:18:29,458
[DAICHI] The portal device
will be complete soon.

315
00:18:29,541 --> 00:18:33,000
However, I need more time
to consider the Noah Project.

316
00:18:33,083 --> 00:18:35,375
That's not for us scientists
to decide.

317
00:18:35,458 --> 00:18:37,958
I am a human
before I'm a scientist!

318
00:18:38,041 --> 00:18:39,416
[TAIYO grunts]

319
00:18:39,500 --> 00:18:40,375
Come on.

320
00:18:41,416 --> 00:18:43,583
[TAIYO sighs]
I don't care what you do.

321
00:18:43,666 --> 00:18:44,583
Do what you want.

322
00:18:44,666 --> 00:18:45,541
Hold on.

323
00:18:45,625 --> 00:18:47,000
One thing,

324
00:18:47,083 --> 00:18:50,166
just make sure you run
those tests on the portal.

325
00:18:50,250 --> 00:18:53,250
If you deliberately slow down
the research for any reason,

326
00:18:53,333 --> 00:18:55,666
you know what happens.

327
00:18:55,750 --> 00:18:57,666
Look, leave it to me.

328
00:18:57,750 --> 00:18:58,958
Don't worry, okay?

329
00:19:13,708 --> 00:19:15,750
I'm sorry
about all of this, Akira.

330
00:19:15,833 --> 00:19:17,583
Go ahead, get back
to Yuki, okay?

331
00:19:17,666 --> 00:19:19,541
♪

332
00:19:28,791 --> 00:19:30,916
It's finally time.

333
00:19:31,000 --> 00:19:32,000
[TSUKI]
Yes.

334
00:19:41,291 --> 00:19:43,333
[DAICHI] The safety devices
are all operational.

335
00:19:43,416 --> 00:19:44,958
It'll be fine.

336
00:19:45,041 --> 00:19:47,375
But, in order to prevent them
from using this for evil,

337
00:19:47,458 --> 00:19:50,208
I have to confirm
my hypothesis.

338
00:19:50,291 --> 00:19:52,625
That's why this test
is necessary.

339
00:19:52,708 --> 00:19:54,750
[keyboard keys clacking]

340
00:19:54,833 --> 00:19:56,666
♪

341
00:20:07,458 --> 00:20:08,416
[grunts]

342
00:20:08,500 --> 00:20:10,375
Hey! What the...

343
00:20:10,458 --> 00:20:11,708
-[keyboard keys clacking]
-[beeping]

344
00:20:11,791 --> 00:20:13,750
None of the safety devices
are working.

345
00:20:13,833 --> 00:20:14,750
But why?

346
00:20:14,833 --> 00:20:15,666
Shit!

347
00:20:15,750 --> 00:20:16,791
He did this!

348
00:20:20,666 --> 00:20:22,291
[grunting]

349
00:20:23,458 --> 00:20:24,791
This is bad.

350
00:20:24,875 --> 00:20:27,000
It's gonna surpass
the critical state.

351
00:20:31,958 --> 00:20:33,250
Yuki.

352
00:20:33,333 --> 00:20:34,708
Souma.

353
00:20:34,791 --> 00:20:37,791
♪

354
00:20:37,875 --> 00:20:39,791
[grunting]

355
00:20:39,875 --> 00:20:42,333
Miss Yuki!

356
00:20:42,416 --> 00:20:43,416
Akira.

357
00:20:44,625 --> 00:20:47,083
♪

358
00:20:56,125 --> 00:20:57,791
[gasps]

359
00:20:57,875 --> 00:20:59,000
[TSUBASA]
Yoshiaki.

360
00:21:00,458 --> 00:21:01,458
[gasps]

361
00:21:01,541 --> 00:21:02,958
[cheering]

362
00:21:03,041 --> 00:21:04,791
♪

363
00:21:17,000 --> 00:21:21,291
[DAICHI] In the end,
I wasn't able to save anyone.

364
00:21:21,375 --> 00:21:24,208
♪

365
00:21:30,666 --> 00:21:32,750
But this, I know.

366
00:21:35,541 --> 00:21:38,166
This at least wasn't a mistake.

367
00:21:40,750 --> 00:21:42,791
There's still a chance.

368
00:21:42,875 --> 00:21:44,291
I know there is.

369
00:21:46,083 --> 00:21:47,416
Reach for it.

370
00:21:51,416 --> 00:21:52,291
[gasps]

371
00:23:36,958 --> 00:23:38,750
♪

372
00:23:38,833 --> 00:23:40,041
[inaudible]

373
00:23:43,625 --> 00:23:45,958
[TAKUYA]
Next episode, "Decision."

